title: For Sale:  Glock 24  --  Very rare  --  Must see
postcontent:
The 24 was introduced in 1994 as a competition variant of the 22. It is the longest Glock ever manufactured. It has a factory compensated long slide that’s just shy of 9” and a 6” barrel. A small amount of these guns were produced and they are no longer in production. 

This gun is one of a kind and out of all the handguns I have shot this one is definitely my favorite. (im more than willing to meet at a range so you can see for yourself) Recoil is very minimal, barrel rise is not an issue at all. I have done many rapid fire shoots where my shots were touching each other. The accuracy of the gun is amazing (first group I shot with it was better than any I have done with my 1911)

The only 24 I have ever seen for sale was at Gun World and it was completely stock except for a KKM barrel, they wanted $1400 for it. I have seen a few online from time to time prices ranging from $650-$800

Here is a list of everything that is done to the gun and included. I did a google search to find the lowest online prices for each item. 

6” KKM Precision Match barrel - $175
Ghost trigger connector and spring kit - $40
TRUGLO Tritium / Fiber Optic sights (TG131GT1) -$90
HEINIE Glock Clasic black sight set - $75
Grip stippling by GPI custom gunworks (sides, back, finger groves, trigger guard, mag release) - $150
Extended slide stop - $15
Extended mag release - $10
Protec Elite 190 lumen light - $50
(5) 15 round factory Glock magazines - $150
120 rounds of FMJ  -  30 rounds of HP - $50

$805 Invested into the gun

I am incredibly attached to this gun and swore that I would never sell it but I really need money to put towards a vehicle so I guess it’s time for someone else to enjoy it. I am selling it as a package deal, I am willing to hear out most reasonable offers but I know what I have, what it is worth and If I can’t get enough money for it then I’ll just keep it.

ASKING $1300
